Reasoning: The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to analyze videos captured from egocentric and surveillance cameras. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graph matching and optimization techniques, which fall under the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper deals with privacy and security concerns related to surveillance videos, which could fall under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
